    <div class="galleryCell galleryCell-3">
    	<a href="photos/lapalma/2021eruption/0930/lavafromclose.html"><img class="galleryImg" src="https://volcanodiscovery.de/fileadmin/photos/canaries/2021/lapalma0930/lapalma_k31915_s.jpg" width="360" height="240" alt="With a special permit from the Civil Protection, Tom and a few other members of the Volcanological Society were granted short time access to the area in upper El Paraiso close to the vent.
During the day, activity had been at stable levels similar to the previous days, with continuous lava fountains from the flank vent, associated with effusion of several overlapping lava flows, as well as pulsating moderate jets of gas, ash and some lava bombs from the upper vents.
This activity changed short time after we had left in the later evening, with the opening of new vents and new lava flows further to the north of the ones seen here, destroying the places shown or at least making them inaccessible afterwards. (Photo: Tom Pfeiffer)" /></a>
