An underwater eruption occurred off the northern coast in around 1700 AD. 
Methana is known for its hot springs and uncrowded, beautiful green rural landscape. Team member photographer Tobias Schorr who has lived more than 10 years in Methana and knows the peninsula better than anyone recently spent countless hours documenting each of the more than 30 lava domes of Methana with his drone from the air. Here are the results: (Photo: Tobias Schorr)" /></a>
