    <div class="galleryCell galleryCell-3">
    	<a href="https://www.volcanoadventures.com//tours/danakil/nov2016/impressions.html"><img class="galleryImg" src="https://volcanodiscovery.de/fileadmin/photos/user/HJ/P1020706_s.jpg" width="360" height="270" alt="The first of our Danakil expeditions of the 2016-2017 winter season turned out to be an unexpected success - not only because of the flawless logistics and organisation or the friendliness with which local Ethiopians welcome international travelers, but also thanks to the very high activity at Erta Ale and Dallol! 
At Erta Ale, the lava lake has been overflowing multiple times a day, sometimes even continuously, constructing a large new area of fresh pahoehoe lava flows on the caldera floor. Our main guide and organiser, Ethiopian geologist Enku, has been regularly visiting this location but never saw it this active and impressive in his 20 years experience. 
And also Dallol seems to have stepped up its game: after the slow drying out and shrinking of the hydrothermal activity at this unique location between 2010 and 2015, last years rains had transformed it back to is former colourful and fascinating self - and this active area is still growing even in the past few weeks. 
Below we gladly share with you a number of images that our participants Hans en Jooske kindly send us days after returning home from their Danakil volcano adventure. (Photo: Hans and Jooske)" /></a>
